# Dev Workflow

## Package Management

- **Only `uv`** — never `pip install` directly
- Add deps: `uv add <package>`
- Run tools: `uv run --frozen <command>` (always pass `--frozen` to avoid rewriting `uv.lock`)
- Sync env: `uv sync`

## Common Commands

```bash
make run        # uv run --frozen polymarket-mcp
make test       # uv run --frozen pytest
make inspector  # npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector
make build      # docker build -t polymarket-mcp .
make start      # docker run -p 8000:8000
```

## Docker

- Package installed via `uv sync --frozen` in the image
- Server entrypoint: `uv run --frozen polymarket-mcp`
- Server listens on port 8000 (`streamable-http`)

## Testing

Run `make test`. Uses pytest with respx for HTTP mocking.

## Dependencies

Declare direct dependencies in `pyproject.toml` if imported in source (e.g. `httpx`, `pydantic-settings`), not only as transitive deps of `mcp`.
